00060 int main(int argc, char* argv[])
00061 {
00062 
00063  RT_Main* rMain;
00064  rMain = new RT_Main("apt-rt-chp-to-txt");
00065 
00066  if ( !Fs::dirExists("test-generated") ) {
00067    Fs::mkdir("test-generated", false);
00068  }
00069 
00070 
00071  rMain->setVar("sdk_top", "../../..");
00072  rMain->setVar("gold_lib", "${gold_dir}/lib");
00073 
00074  if(argc < 1)
00075    {
00076      cout<<"Error: Incorrect number of arguments given"<<endl;
00077      exit(1);
00078    }
00079  //They want us to run all default tests
00080  else if(argc == 1)
00081    {
00082      rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoMpam());
00083      rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoBrlmm());
00084      rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoDm());
00085      rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaExpMas5());
00086      rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoMpamBad());
00087    }
00088  else
00089    {
00090      rMain->parseArgv(argc, argv);
00091 
00092      cout<<"Running Built-In Regression Tests"<<endl;
00093 
00094      if(rMain->getVarVal("doCdfXdaGenoMpam") != "")
00095        {
00096          rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoMpam());
00097        }
00098      if(rMain->getVarVal("doCdfXdaGenoBrlmm") != "")
00099        {
00100          rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoBrlmm());
00101        }
00102      if(rMain->getVarVal("doCdfXdaGenoDm") != "")
00103        {
00104          rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoDm());
00105        }
00106      if(rMain->getVarVal("doCdfXdaExpMas5") != "")
00107        {
00108          rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaExpMas5());
00109        }
00110      if(rMain->getVarVal("doCdfXdaGenoMpamBad") != "")
00111        {
00112          rMain->addTest(doCdfXdaGenoMpamBad());
00113        }
00114    }
00115  rMain->runTests();
00116 }

00119 RT_Test* doTest(const std::string &testName, const std::string &fileName, const std::string &cdfFile)
00120 {
00121   RT_Test* rt;
00122   rt = new RT_Test(testName);
00123 
00124   RT_Cmd* cmd = rt->newCmd();
00125   cmd->setExe("${apt_chp_to_txt}");
00126   cmd->addArg("--out-dir", "${out_testname}");
00127   cmd->addArg("--cdf-file", cdfFile);
00128   cmd->addArg("${gold_dir}/util/chp-to-txt/chp/" + fileName);
00129 
00130   RT_Check* check = rt->newCheck();
00131   check->setExe("${apt_check_mixedfile}");
00132   check->addArg("--gen", "${out_testname}/" + fileName + ".txt");
00133   check->addArg("--gold", Fs::join("${gold_dir}/util/chp-to-txt",testName,fileName + ".txt"));
00134   check->addArg("--epsilon", "0.00001");
00135   check->addArg("--skipLines", "0");
00136   check->addArg("--allowedMismatch", "0");
00137   
00138   return rt;
00139 }

00142 RT_Test* doBadChipTypeTest(const std::string &testName, const std::string &fileName, const std::string &cdfFile)
00143 {
00144   RT_Test* rt;
00145   rt = new RT_Test(testName);
00146   
00147   RT_Cmd* cmd = rt->newCmd();
00148   cmd->setExe("${apt_chp_to_txt}");
00149   cmd->addArg("-v");
00150   cmd->addArg("-1");
00151   cmd->addArg("--out-dir", "${out_testname}");
00152   cmd->addArg("--cdf-file", cdfFile);
00153   cmd->addArg("${gold_dir}/util/chp-to-txt/chp/" + fileName);
00154 
00155   //Negative Test
00156   rt->setExpectedRetVal(1);
00157 
00158   return rt;
00159 }
